  {
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Hi @JugglerX,\r\n\r\nThank you for raising this issue.\r\n\r\nThis is due to having the same instance of `InstantSearch` across two different pages, as it's declared in `_app.tsx` so it wraps the page.\r\n\r\nYou can circumvent this by adding a `key` to `InstantSearch`, so that there is a dedicated instance per page. You could add this to [your `Default.tsx` file, line 93](https://github.com/JugglerX/bal-router/blob/52703050bb2163dfbdcb7b10063201bc4953b56d/src/layouts/Default.tsx#L93) : \r\n```js\r\nkey={router.pathname}\r\n```",
